## Definitions

- **Breach of security safeguards** — PIPEDA s. 10.1 definition.
- **Real risk of significant harm (RROSH)** — PIPEDA threshold for
  mandatory reporting.
- **Suspicious activity (SA)** — facts giving reasonable grounds to
  suspect a transaction relates to money-laundering or terrorist-
  financing.
- **Sanctions hit** — match against the consolidated Canadian
  sanctions list (administered through OSFI).

A single incident may attract more than one regulatory pathway —
e.g., a credential-stuffing attack against a brokerage account
leaves a PIPEDA-reportable breach **and** a FINTRAC-reportable
suspicious-transaction record if the attacker initiated withdrawals.

